        <section id="project4">
            <h2>BAG BIRKIN</h2>
            <p><strong>Award:</strong> CSS Design Awards</p>
            <p><strong>URL:</strong> <a href="https://bagbirkin.tilda.ws/en#rec777186705" target="_blank">Visit BAG BIRKIN</a></p>
            <p><strong>Analysis:</strong> 
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Collage-style images:</strong> Unlike traditional presentations of luxury brands, the use of images as if they were part of a collage gives the site a very creative aesthetic. Instead of refined or super elegant images, the collage gives a fresher and more authentic feel, breaking expectations and creating an unexpected visual experience.</li>
                    <li><strong>Typography:</strong> I really liked the combination of different fonts, especially the contrast between the use of an elegant serif font and a handwritten-like sans serif font.</li>
                    <li><strong>Color palette:</strong> I really like the use of an off-white combined with dark grays and a red/orange tone.</li>
                    <li><strong>Horizontal scrolling:</strong> As the user navigates the page, they reach a section where the scroll direction changes to horizontal, creating a carousel-like effect that makes the navigation more dynamic and creative.</li>
                    <li><strong>Interactivity:</strong> The site includes an interactive section where the user can move different Birkin bags and "try them" on a human figure. This type of interaction personalizes the user experience.</li>
                </ul>
